User no longer passes a `registration-options` settings but a `scope` setting

Makes it more explicit and understandable by abstracting away the complexity of what are the available options for a Service Worker registration.

Default value of registration-options is now an empty object, and not a hardcoded scope

This lets us always fall back on the browser's implementation of default scope

Fetch the original request

We was changing the request by using the URL directly and changing CORS.
By fetching the original request we do almost nothing differently if the request was to succeed.

See: https://jakearchibald.com/2016/service-workers-and-base-uris/
